<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-69-0721 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper concerns predicting the potential for reclamation success onland destined for disturbance and judging the success of reclamationattempts on land already disturbed. It reviews current American methodologyfor determining revegetation success of surface mined land and presentsan alternative approach. The author's discussion especially applies tosurface mined land, but it will become apparent that the principles involvedare universal and applicable to other kinds of disturbance.</TEXT></DOC>